iThe part that stuck out to me was the concept of free speech and		gopher.black	70
iprotected speech, their terminology, and the psychology involved		gopher.black	70
iin each. Yargo, in a simplistic and unfair summary to him, stated		gopher.black	70
ithat he'd prefer to say whatever he likes without fear of legal		gopher.black	70
iconsequences. That's a great place to start.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThere is some psychological system at play which places the idea		gopher.black	70
iof protection on the individuals who are criticized, or who are		gopher.black	70
ithe subject of hate speech. Media discussions surround the idea of		gopher.black	70
isensitivity and others refer to "snowflakes". Protection is		gopher.black	70
idemanded by the sensitive, or so it seems.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iWe know in reality that it is the speech which is the subject to		gopher.black	70
iprotection instead. It is not the targets of the speech, but the		gopher.black	70
ispeaker who needs focus here, right?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThe distinction is minor because the relationship between the		gopher.black	70
ispeaker and target haven't changed. But that's not the whole		gopher.black	70
istory, is it? If we use terms like "free speech" it hides part of		gopher.black	70
ithe story. When we say "protected speech" now we get at the crux.		gopher.black	70
iProtected by whom, and from whom?		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iThere are other parties involved: the speaker, the subject, and		gopher.black	70
ithe protective entity and the persecutive entity. So when we look		gopher.black	70
iback at the discussion of protected speech now we can fit everyone		gopher.black	70
iinto context:		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iA speaker's (subject) speech toward someone (object) is		gopher.black	70
ipotentially protected (protector) from persecution (persecutor).		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iWho is the persecutor? In the case of the United States and the		gopher.black	70
i1st amendment from which most of this discussion flows for		gopher.black	70
iAmericans it is the US government itself.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iWho is the protector? Well, again in this case, the US government.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i  Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of		gopher.black	70
i  religion, or prohibiting the free exercise thereof; or abridging		gopher.black	70
i  the freedom of speech, or of the press; or the right of the		gopher.black	70
